[3] Liberia: Ebola treatment unit workers protest
Date: Sat 30 May 2015
Source: Front Page Africa [edited]
http://www.frontpageafricaonline.com/index.php/news/5366-ebola-treatment-unit-workers-protest-hazard-benefits


Ebola treatment unit workers have staged another protest in demand for hazard benefits from the Government of Liberia. After the Ebola crisis in Liberia, people involved in the fight against the deadly Ebola virus that killed more than 4000 Liberians have been protesting, demanding hazard benefits.

Holding placards in front of the president's office at the Foreign Ministry, the group through their spokesperson James Baysay said they are from different ETUs [Ebola treatment units] including ELWA, the Unity Conference Center, Island Clinic and Old Defense Ministry, and they gathered to remind President Ellen Johnson Sirleaf of the alleged promise that she was going to call them after 3 days when they gathered close to her residence on 14 May [2015] to demand benefits.

"We went to her residence, and she told us that she was going to call us in 3 days' time, but since then, we have not received any call from her. The government should have given us our benefits. When we met the president last week on Thu [28 May 2015], she promised that she was going to call us, but up to now, we have not received any call from her yet, so we have come to remind her," Baysay said.

He recalled that during the turning over ceremony at ELWA, they were also present at that occasion, and they were able to put forth their demands but said they were advised to put their demands in writing, something, which according to him, was done. But still their demands have not been met ...

[byline: Massa F Kanneh]

