[5] Suspected, research, funding

1 Jun 2015 Guinea-Bissau: Ebola threat to Guinea-Bissau rises as border zone heats up
http://www.trust.org/item/20150601232159-np3bh/
[Continuing violent protests against anti-Ebola controls in north Guinea have prompted the Red Cross to withdraw workers, undermining efforts to stop the spread of Ebola into neighboring Guinea-Bissau, with which Guinea shares a border. After no new Ebola cases in months, there are 6 new cases reported in north Guinea's Boke prefecture. According to the World Health Organization, one Ebola contact is thought to be in Guinea-Bissau. Two Red Cross cars and an employee's home were attacked, and a warehouse containing equipment for safe Ebola burials, considered critical to containing the virus, was incinerated.]

1 Jun 2015 Nigeria: Bauchi State Pilgrims to undergo Ebola and meningitis screening
http://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2015/06/01/hajj-bauchi-pilgrims-to-undergo-ebola-meningitis-screening/
[All Hajj pilgrims from Bauchi State, Nigeria to Saudi Arabia will undergo screening for the Ebola virus disease, meningitis, and Lassa fever. Hajj is expected to fall between 21-26 Sep 2015.]

1 Jun 2015 Sierra Leone: Lawmaker held over unsafe burial in Ebola-hit Sierra Leone
http://www.news24.com/Africa/News/Lawmaker-held-over-unsafe-burial-in-Ebola-hit-Sierra-Leone-20150601
[Alie Badara, from the northern district of Kambia, has been arrested for suspicion of taking part in a traditional burial ceremony on 29 May 2015 without informing the authorities of the death, according to Assistant Inspector-General Fuk Daboh.]

1 Jun 2015 USA (Maryland): Patient in Baltimore evaluated for Ebola symptoms
http://www.wbaltv.com/health/patient-in-baltimore-evaluated-for-ebola-symptoms/33333278
[A patient is being evaluated at Johns Hopkins Hospital in Baltimore for Ebola-like symptoms (a high fever) following a recent return from West Africa. Although the 1st test returned negative, as a precaution, the patient is being held in isolation until definitive testing results are received. According to Health Department officials, there is no danger to the public.]

3 Jun 2015 USA (Texas): Why didn't Ebola spread inside this Dallas apartment?
http://thescoopblog.dallasnews.com/2015/06/why-didnt-ebola-spread-inside-this-dallas-apartment.html
[The inside story of the Dallas index case by his partner]

